content.description:
Was 10c before holds broke off

This is another short climb at the end of the pipeline.  Crux is figuring out the sequence below the buldge using a really small gaston and a pretty crappy pinchy sloper.
content.location: Second to last route in the pipeline area.  Shares chains with poop chute.

content.description: Crux is low, make your way up some marginal hold to the big hole, make a few more long moves and get to the jugs under the roof, shake it out, then finish it out.
Bouldery start to a good rest to an overhanging crimper topout.
content.location:
In the middle of the crag, can be located by a huge undercling cobble below the 2nd bolt and a drilled pocket (at maple?) to the left of the 4rd bolt.  Video beta can be found at:

urbanclimbermag.tv/videos/vâ€¦

content.description: Just recently part of a good hold came off. It requires a hard move from right to left, then up some crimpers to a sweet sidepull, then to a hard-to-see handle bar. Once you grab the poop chute you're done.
content.location: The most far right climb in The Pipeline.

content.description: A well traveled hard 11. The crux is near the roof but you're saved by well placed pocket. The whole climb is in your face and awesome.
content.location:
This climb is to the left of

Crescent Moon

.

content.description: The first 3-4 bolts is some tricky handwork. Then it lets up with a very fun last 2 bolts.
Crux is pulling up and over the roof to good holds.  The movement on this route is smooth and flows great!  Don't miss it.
content.location: Right of Crescent Moon and left of Laying Pipe.

content.description: Nice easy climbing with a couple of huge jugs to rest on before the roof.  The crux comes at the roof.  The last bolt is in your face and hard to clip.  It is far easier to clip from above (or skip) if you don't mind the exposure.  Bump through sequencey crimps with large committing moves and pull over the roof.
content.location: Just left of Lip Venom and right of Plumbers Crack.  Towards the far end of the wall.

content.description: Ascend in a jaunty fashion then stare at a big throw to the Honey Bucket. The guidebook says 12a. Consensus is that it is a very soft 12a. Climb it and rate it yourself.
Crux is low, get into a cruddy under cling, high step and make your way to a cruddy ear, then throw to a jug. Keep it together for the easier climbing at the top.
A V4 boulder problem at the start (passing the 2nd bolt), gives way to some large holes & jugs for a shake-out. Gun it with big moves from large, fun holds to the top
content.location: Just right of Predator. Use to have red hangers-there's remnants of red paint still on some hangers

content.description:
Steep and very bouldery to start with some very long moves.

Start up jugs to an undercling and move into a left facing jug and the second bolt. Make a big move up to a right side pull and figure out how to let go with your left hand to get a really wide pinch and the third clip. Another big move off of the pinch take you up jugs to the break below the final small bulge and vertical face to finish. A long pull over the bulge gets the side of a big broken off cobble then standard edges up the face to the anchors.
content.protection: Bolts to a bolted anchor with FIXE rings.
content.location: This is the 6th route from the left end of the crag. Also the second of the steeper lines right of the lower angle scooped out section where the two 5.10's are.

content.description: This is kind of an awkward climb.  The crux is right at the beginning to the second bolt, then it lets up.
content.location: It's the second line after you walk into the pipeline.  Right of The Angry Inch 5.11c, and left of Liquid Zipper 5.10d.

content.description: This starts vertical and slowly starts to overhang to a tricky sequential roof. The roof is the crux with bumping crimps. This climb requires focused power. No rests but it's short.
content.location: 6th climb from the right. In this area climbers have chalked in the rating below the climb.

content.description: Crap-O. Yeah there are some challenging holds on the route that brings to mind, "Thats a crappy hold!" This is a quality route with great movement from the beginning to end. Begin with breathless moves to jugs then crimps while gravity takes its toll.
content.location: First route (Left to right). Left of the Angry Inch.

content.description: This is a fun route with a hold about 3/4 of the way up that is a broken cobble, sharp as a tomato slicer.
content.location: this route is to the right of the 10d warmup route

content.description: This is a very classic climb.  Very steep and fun!!  The .11c rating comes from the first 10 feet of the climb. Then after that, nothing is harder than a .11a.
content.location: Second route from the left as you enter the pipeline.
